    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Who it's for</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">Who should use Koala AI — <span class="accent">and who shouldn't.</span></h2>
      <p>The clearest filter we found after real-world testing across content types.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">Buy Koala AI if</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">You're an affiliate marketer or niche publisher.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Three signals Koala AI is the right fit.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>You build Amazon affiliate or product review sites</h4><p>The ASIN-based review mode genuinely saves hours per article compared to any alternative.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>You review every article before publishing</h4><p>Real-time data helps, but all AI content still needs fact-checking — especially for health, legal, or financial topics.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>You have keyword research covered separately</h4><p>Ahrefs or Semrush for strategy, Koala for execution. The two-tool stack makes sense if you're serious about search.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
