          <div class="faq-answer">KoalaWriter generates long-form articles using word credits and SERP analysis. KoalaChat is a separate conversational assistant with real-time web search and file analysis, running on its own message quota — heavy chat usage doesn't drain your writing credits.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How does the word credit system work?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Each plan includes monthly word credits. GPT-5 Mini costs 1 credit per word; premium models like GPT-5.2 or Claude 4.5 Sonnet cost 2 credits per word. A 2,000-word article at premium rates burns 4,000 credits — so you get half the articles you'd expect.</div>
